  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Towards Pro-poor &amp; Progressive Tax System in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project will be useful to achieve goals mentioned under Oxfam country strategy through scaling up the impact by connecting local level issues with national level and take it to upper level as appropriate. Project activities will include public engagement through social media, stakeholder consultations, research and dissemination, media engagement, lobby and different kinds of influencing work. The campaign aims to build broader alliance of citizen groups so that it can be part of the people&apos;s movement. Therefore it has given emphasis on imitating dialogue at different level to broader citizen movement for establishing tax and fiscal justice in Bangladesh. The campaign strategy initiate actions on three corresponding processes of knowledge building, capacity building of grassroots campaign and engagement with National board of revenue of Government with a series of campaign for knowledge building, grassroots mobilisation, research, advocacy, networking and alliance building at national, regional and global level.</narrative>
  </description>
